==="indic"===

The Indic script version of the text.  You may use <code>indic2</code> and <code>indic3</code> for alternative spellings in the '''same''' language (although they can be different scripts).  If you need to show a different language, use another instance of this template separated by a semi-colon ';'.

==="trans"===

The transliteration of the source script.  You may use <code>indic2</code> and <code>indic3</code> for alternative spellings in the '''same''' language (although they can be different scripts).  If you need to show a different language, use another instance of this template separated by a semi-colon ';'.

==="defaultipa"===

The IPA text of the pronunciation of the word in English.

==="defaultaudio"===

An audio file indicating the pronunciation of the word in English.

==="indicipa"===

The IPA text of the pronunciation of the word in the source language.

==="indicaudio"===

An audio file indicating the pronunciation of the word in the source language.

